<strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data-conte=
nt-id=3D"1203279602">The API Odyssey</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"a754afe0-7384-4b32-acf3-e4bd6c8d=
0746-1203279602">
<div class=3D"sectionColumnWrapper">
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<div class=3D"columnMacro" style=3D"width:80%;min-width:80%;max-width:80%;"=
>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">This video gives a brief outline of t=
he development lifecycle on the Westpac Mesh Platform. It will take you thr=
ough from developing your API from a swagger specification, building and de=
ploying your code, and then to a how a customer consumes your API.</span></=
p>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"embeddedObject">
<video src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279602/API Odessey.mp4" height=3D"3=
80" width=3D"80%" controls>
Your browser does not support the HTML5 video element
</video>
</div>
<p></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<h2 id=3D"TheAPIOdyssey-Summaryofdevelopmentlifecycle"><strong>Summary of d=
evelopment lifecycle</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>The developer will receive a Swagger specification from his designer. T=
his is the contract that defines your API to consumers.</li>
<li>Using Westpac Mesh Developer tools, we can generate a stub Java project=
 from the swagger specification.</li>
<li>Write your code and unit tests!</li>
<li>Check the code into Bitbucket, our version control system.</li>
<li>This triggers the continuous integration pipeline in Bamboo, which comp=
iles and builds your code and runs your unit tests.</li>
<li>If the tests are successful, the API is loaded into a Docker container =
with Tomcat and Java installed.</li>
<li>The container is pushed to Artifactory, our binary repository manager.<=
/li>
<li>This triggers the continuous delivery pipeline in Bamboo, where the Doc=
ker container is loaded onto the platform.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"TheAPIOdyssey-SummaryofAPIconsumptionbyacustomer"><strong>Summary=
 of API consumption by a customer</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>APIs on the platform are exposed through Axway, our API gateway.</li>
<li>When a request is made, it is directed to NGINX, our load balancer.</li=
>
<li>When an API starts up it is registered in Consul, our service registry.=
</li>
<li>NGINX communicates with Consul to know which Docker container to redire=
ct the request to.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"TheAPIOdyssey-Importantpoints"><strong>Important points</strong><=
/h2>
<ul>
<li>Code generation saves time from writing boilerplate code and includes a=
ll the necessary helper libraries to run on the platform. Additionally, it =
ensures that the code has a direct mapping to the API contract.</li>
<li>You are free to use any IDE that suits your project.</li>
<li>Source check-ins to the master branch of a project will automatically t=
rigger a build and deployment into the Dev1 environment.</li>
<li>In the build pipeline, your unit (eg. Junit) tests are run.</li>
<li>In the deploy pipeline, your integration (eg. Newman/Postman) tests are=
 run.</li>
<li>Multiple instances of any single API can be running simultaneously.</li=
>
<li>The same Swagger specification that you develop from will be used by yo=
ur consumers.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279605">Roles and Responsibilties</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"a754afe0-7384-4b32-acf3-e4bd6c8d=
0746-1203279605">
<div class=3D"sectionColumnWrapper">
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<div class=3D"columnMacro" style=3D"width:80%;min-width:80%;max-width:80%;"=
>
<h2 id=3D"RolesandResponsibilties-Overview"><strong>Overview</strong></h2>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"208" src=3D"8946eb3856717e73ba142892c2e8090560eaf6be2dfc38c106dd742355=
