</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279611">What Development Tools Do You Need?</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"994375ee-4ef4-42a9-911e-c52452d1=
d891-1203279611">
<div class=3D"sectionColumnWrapper">
<div class=3D"sectionMacro">
<div class=3D"sectionMacroRow">
<div class=3D"columnMacro">
<h2 id=3D"WhatDevelopmentToolsDoYouNeed?-Whataccessyouneedtorequest"><stron=
g>What access you need to request</strong></h2>
<p>You will need to request access to these enterprise tools to start devel=
oping on Westpac Mesh:</p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"WhatDevelopmentToolsDoYouNeed?-"><strong><span class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"conf=
luence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" width=3D"468" src=3D"a3b894013fd=
748a927c27448e83acbd49157b38f30c60cb55c4d70d4f113cf90" data-image-src=3D"/d=
ownload/attachments/1203279611/Picture4.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDat=
e=3D1663571137323&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-li=
nked-resource-id=3D"1203279613" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-lin=
ked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"Pict=
ure4.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-link=
ed-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D=
"1203279611" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" height=
=3D"135"></span></strong></h2>
<p><br></p>
<p>Instructions on how to do this can be found at&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://c=
onfluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Developer+Prerequisites" rel=3D"n=
ofollow">Developer Prerequisites</a></p>
<h2 id=3D"WhatDevelopmentToolsDoYouNeed?-Whattoolsdodevelopersneed?"><stron=
g>What tools do developers need?</strong></h2>
<p>We have automated the download and installation of many development tool=
s for you.</p>
<p>Instructions on how to install and run Chocolatey can be found here&nbsp=
;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Develop=
er+Tools" rel=3D"nofollow">Mesh Developer Tools</a></p>
<p><br></p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embed=
ded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"fals=
e" width=3D"468" src=3D"584b8dd52df42b170cbed3d1e4976f5f373884faf0403e129c5=
8071bbceadea5" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279611/Picture5.=
png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571137250&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unr=
esolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279612" data-lin=
ked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-li=
nked-resource-default-alias=3D"Picture5.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confl=
uence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" d=
ata-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279611" data-linked-resource-contai=
ner-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" height=3D"228"></span>
<h2 id=3D"WhatDevelopmentToolsDoYouNeed?-WestpacMeshDeveloperTools"><strong=
>Westpac Mesh Developer Tools</strong></h2>
<p>Westpac Mesh Developer Tools is a command-line tool that will provide ba=
sic capabilities to enable development of components on the Westpac Mesh pl=
atform.</p>
<p>This includes:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Code generation from a Swagger specification</li>
<li>Build and deploy to a Westpac Mesh environment</li>
<li>Run your component locally in a container that simulates a Westpac Mesh=
 environment</li>
<li>Validate the configuration of your component</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279614">API Basics</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"994375ee-4ef4-42a9-911e-c52452d1=
d891-1203279614">
<h1 id=3D"APIBasics-DirectorystructureofyourAPI"><strong>Directory structur=
e of your API</strong></h1>
<p>After your API repository has been created and initialised, it should co=
ntain the following:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>swagger.yaml - this is a sample that you can overwrite with your own</l=
i>
<li><a href=3D"/display/MD/Metadata+Yaml+files">Metadata Yaml files</a>&nbs=
p;- metadata files that describe your component, these are essential for yo=
ur running your API on the platform</li>
<li>env folder - to store environment specific configuration files, files i=
n 'default' will be read first and then overwritten by any named environmen=
t folders</li>
<li>secrets folder - similar to the env folder, this stores encrypted secre=
ts that can only be decrypted by the platform</li>
<li>api-tests - stores your integration tests. You can export your Postman =
tests and save them to a file named 'idempotent_tests_postman_collection.js=
on'</li>
<li>src folder - stores your code, this follows the Maven folder structure =
if you have a Java based project</li>
<li>pom.xml - this is prepopulated with necessary plugins and dependencies =
to run your API on the platform</li>
</ul>
<p>You will need to ensure that the metadata yaml has been populated correc=
tly, and then fill in the remaining empty fields such as displayName and de=
scription in component.yaml.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Find more information about the <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.=
westpac.com.au/display/MD/Metadata+Yaml+files" rel=3D"nofollow">Metadata Ya=
ml files here</a>.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" src=3D"76d023c13df292270c3fa07831f028=
8ce080adf16ee2b81a5cd9effa186705df" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments=
/1203279614/image2021-3-31_14-18-22.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D=
1663571137713&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked=
-resource-id=3D"1203279615" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-=
resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image202=
1-3-31_14-18-22.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au=
" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-cont=
ainer-id=3D"1203279614" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"5" alt=3D=
"" width=3D"264" height=3D"592"></span></p>
<h1 id=3D"APIBasics-Developertools"><strong>Developer tools</strong></h1>
<p>Full documentation for <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/=
display/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools" rel=3D"nofollow">Mesh Developer Tools</a=
>.</p>
<p>Here are some basic commands to get you started:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><pre>mesh -h - display the full list of commands</pre></li>
<li><pre>mesh gencode - generate stub code from your swagger.yaml</pre></li=
>
<li><pre>mesh run - run the API on a local instance of Tomcat</pre></li>
<li><pre>mesh build - trigger a custom build of your project on the CI pipe=
line</pre></li>
<li><pre>mesh deploy - deploy your component to an environment&nbsp;</pre><=
/li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"APIBasics-Deploymentpathway"><strong>Deployment pathway</strong><=
/h1>
<p>Whenever code is merged into the 'master' branch of your project, this t=
riggers an automatic build of your project, and then a deployment into the =
dev1 environment.</p>
<p>A specific build must have been deployed into a lower environment before=
 it can be promoted to a higher environment. All non-production environment=
s are developer self-serve, and can be triggered through Westpac Mesh Devel=
oper Tools.</p>
<p>The order of environments is:</p>
<p>DEV =E2=86=92 SIT =E2=86=92 UAT =E2=86=92 SVP =E2=86=92 PROD</p>
<h1 id=3D"APIBasics-Sonar"><strong>Sonar</strong></h1>
<p>All APIs in Westpac Mesh have Sonar code scan enabled. This will provide=
 metrics on the quality of your code which you can view in the Bitbucket wi=
dget.</p>
<p>Currently there are no quality gates being enforced, it is up to the ind=
ividual project teams to define these.&nbsp;</p>
<p>You can find more information about <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.we=
stpac.com.au/display/MD/SonarQube+Integration" rel=3D"nofollow">Sonar here<=
/a>.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"95" src=3D"ff725aa0c6652502283da9974184ba3678257c2f1f3823493fd211c42ce=
d1f74" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279614/image2021-5-17_11=
-28-26.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571137790&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279616" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-5-17_11-28-26.png" data-bas=
e-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279614" data-=
linked-resource-container-version=3D"5" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279617">Incubator Environment</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"994375ee-4ef4-42a9-911e-c52452d1=
d891-1203279617">
<p>This is essentially a sandbox environment for developers to get started =
and experiment with Westpac Mesh.</p>
<ul style=3D"">
<li>To create, deploy and use your API/Component, follow the steps outlined=
&nbsp;<a style=3D"" href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/M=
ESH/Creating+a+Component+in+the+Incubator+Environment" rel=3D"nofollow">her=
e</a></li>
<li>To use the API/Component after it has been cleaned up, simply deploy it=
 again.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"IncubatorEnvironment-AdvantagestousingIncubator"><strong>Advantag=
es to using Incubator</strong></h2>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Any developer with the pre-requisite tools can create an API and deploy=
 it to the&nbsp;Westpac Mesh platform</li>
<li>No governance is required</li>
<li>Can integrate to existing APIs that are deployed in Dev</li>
<li>Begin development before Swagger has been signed</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"IncubatorEnvironment-Cleanup"><strong>Clean up</strong></h2>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Inactive Components in Incubator are regularly cleaned up - for reposit=
ories with no commits for 30 days. An email reminder will be sent before th=
is happens.&nbsp;</li>
<li>Daily clean-up of the environment as described<span>&nbsp;</span><a sty=
le=3D"" href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Schedule=
d+clean+up+of+API+Incubator+environment" rel=3D"nofollow">here</a></li>
<li>You will likely have a clone of the code on your local in the case of r=
epository deletion</li>
</ul>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279619">Exercise: Deploying an API to the Incubator Envi=
ronment</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"994375ee-4ef4-42a9-911e-c52452d1=
d891-1203279619">
<p>In this exercise, we will guide you through deploying an API in the Incu=
bator environment. You will follow a similar process when initialising othe=
r projects in Westpac Mesh.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Exercise:DeployinganAPItotheIncubatorEnvironment-Prerequisites"><=
strong>Prerequisites</strong></h2>
<p>Make sure you have access to Bitbucket and Bamboo.</p>
<p>Download and install the recommended development tools with the automate=
d Chocolatey install: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/disp=
lay/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools" rel=3D"nofollow">Mesh Developer Tools</a>.</=
p>
<p>Download and install the&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.=
com.au/display/MESH/Mesh+Developer+Tools" rel=3D"nofollow">Mesh Developer T=
ools</a>.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Exercise:DeployinganAPItotheIncubatorEnvironment-Initialisethepro=
ject"><strong>Initialise the project</strong></h2>
<p>Open Command Prompt, then from your chosen development folder run:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">mesh inc=
ubate</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>This will open a wizard to guide you through the process. Select the def=
ault settings, specifying a Component shortname of your choice.</p>
<p>Completing the wizard will trigger a pipeline which will create the&nbsp=
;Bitbucket repository and clone it to your local.</p>
<p>Note that you will be prompted for your Bitbucket/Bamboo password during=
 this wizard.</p>
<p>Follow the onscreen instructions to browse to your Component folder.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"305" src=3D"b84f8549fe3978a07bef2a547d44ab887311ee47a180607af1bc624c80=
92191e" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279619/image2021-8-9_15=
-28-51.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571138750&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279622" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-8-9_15-28-51.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279619" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"5" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"Exercise:DeployinganAPItotheIncubatorEnvironment-EdittheSwagger">=
<strong>Edit the Swagger</strong></h2>
<p>If everything went smoothly, your folder should contain a sample swagger=
.yaml and some other .yaml files which describe your project.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"298" src=3D"13ada9e340d904962a62714817e21866c7da8e090e2f23c587a949cd04=
46b7ed" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279619/image2021-8-9_15=
-30-32.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571138647&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279621" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-8-9_15-30-32.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279619" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"5" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p>Now we will make some edits to swagger.yaml. You can use the&nbsp;<a hre=
f=3D"https://swagger.mesh.westpac.com.au/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"n=
ofollow">Swagger Editor</a>&nbsp;to make things easier.</p>
<p>Edit the title and description to something of your choosing.</p>
<p>Now open component.yaml.</p>
<p>This file, along with the other .yaml files, helps configure your compon=
ent to run on Westpac Mesh. component.yaml in particular, describes how you=
r component will be viewed in Mesh Connect.</p>
<p>Add the displayName and description, as you did with the swagger.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Exercise:DeployinganAPItotheIncubatorEnvironment-Generatethecode"=
><strong>Generate the code</strong></h2>
<p>Now run with the default settings:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">mesh gen=
code</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>After this is complete, you should see a /src folder and pom.xml have be=
en added. A standard maven project has now been generated for you.</p>
<p>If you want, you can now open this project in a IDE of your choice.</p>
<p>You can see that many classes have been generated for you, based on what=
 was defined in the Swagger specification.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"260" src=3D"4f8c1b7bb622060fce5bf3b4dea83b03c18f46f43ccc13c0865cb398b2=
918836" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279619/image2021-3-31_1=
6-11-18.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571139143&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279630" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-3-31_16-11-18.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279619" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"5" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"Exercise:DeployinganAPItotheIncubatorEnvironment-Runonlocal"><str=
ong>Run on local</strong></h2>
<p>Now lets actually run the API on our local:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">mesh run=
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>This will start up a Tomcat container, with the same configuration that =
a container running on Westpac Mesh would have.</p>
<p>If successful, a link to the /healthcheck will be displayed.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Exercise:DeployinganAPItotheIncubatorEnvironment-TestinlocalwithP=
ostman"><strong>Test in local with Postman</strong></h2>
<p>Open Postman, and make a GET request to /healthcheck. A HTTP 200 respons=
e will be returned if your API is running.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"282" src=3D"b6247eb2b7202f3b020fc8cf8f607409710c8dd46a959d3c753472e960=
90ed0e" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279619/image2021-3-31_1=
6-23-39.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571139097&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279629" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-3-31_16-23-39.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279619" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"5" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p>Modify the endpoint to /sampleResources as defined in the Swagger and co=
nfirm that is also returning a response.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Exercise:DeployinganAPItotheIncubatorEnvironment-DeploytotheIncub=
atorenvironment"><strong>Deploy to the Incubator environment</strong></h2>
<p>Close the running container with Ctrl-C.</p>
<p>We should commit our changes and push them to the remote repository. You=
 can use your IDE to do this, or use git from the command line.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">git add =
*
git commit -m "Commit generated classes"
git push</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>Now we will attempt to deploy to the Incubator environment:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: sql; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">mesh bui=
ld</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>A few links will be displayed on screen.</p>
<p>The first is a link to the Bamboo plan that is running the CI/CD. View t=
his link, it should look something like this:</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"371" src=3D"53ac6fc4ee7e5ff67e7ef03bc176839d760926c4114dfb4cdb7f83e26a=
fb4b7a" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279619/image2021-8-9_15=
-55-47.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571138570&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279620" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-8-9_15-55-47.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279619" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"5" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p>When the build completes (goes green), your component will have been dep=
loyed to Incubator!</p>
<h2 id=3D"Exercise:DeployinganAPItotheIncubatorEnvironment-TestintheIncubat=
orenvironment"><strong>Test in the Incubator environment</strong></h2>
<p>The links contain the base URL for your API, but let's try another metho=
d to test this out.</p>
<p>The final link is a environment definition file for the Incubator enviro=
nment. Load this, and then import into Postman.</p>
<p>Now find /api-tests/default/idempotent_tests_postman_collection.json in =
your project directory.</p>
<p>You will be populating this file with your integration tests in future. =
For now it only contains the /healthcheck, import this into Postman.</p>
<p>In Postman, change your environment to 'dev1-incubator', and make a GET =
request to the /healthcheck that you imported.</p>
<p>If you get a HTTP 200 response, your API has been successfully deployed =
to the Incubator environment!</p>
<h2 id=3D"Exercise:DeployinganAPItotheIncubatorEnvironment-Bonustask"><stro=
ng>Bonus task</strong></h2>
<p>Modify the endpoint to /sampleResources as we did earlier and make a req=
uest. Sadly, this will not work and we got a 400 Bad Request.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"190" src=3D"f94d76624f66e0ef7079dc302146d6a5ea20e0caa09004e0405809ac2c=
79be90" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279619/image2021-3-31_1=
6-47-35.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571138903&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279625" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-3-31_16-47-35.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279619" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"5" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p>If you compare this to our Swagger specification, you can see that our r=
equest in Postman is missing few mandatory headers.</p>
<p>Many of these headers are required by the Westpac Mesh platform and must=
 be part of all requests. This is enforced by the gateway, and not checked =
when running on your local.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"439" src=3D"c3e2f934ef330420e8e8624e10e80f7c32c033f4a93c8f6433fce012f0=
81a556" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279619/image2021-3-31_1=
6-49-39.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571138850&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279624" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-3-31_16-49-39.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279619" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"5" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p>Add the missing headers and some sensible values to your request. Note t=
hat the query parameter brandSilo is also missing, add this too.</p>
<p>You should get a 200 OK response with a payload if you updated your requ=
est correctly.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"244" src=3D"028a3b5c006dbb8fe08a3012a14c429fe3dc4bb1c3701b77a3e06cf6b6=
b764d0" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279619/image2021-4-1_10=
-28-11.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571138800&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279623" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-4-1_10-28-11.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279619" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"5" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p>From here you can:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Add a test to your request&nbsp;</li>
<li>Save the request to your postman collection</li>
<li>Export the collection to json</li>
<li>Save this into your idempotent tests.</li>
</ul>
<p>This will come in useful for writing tests in your future development wo=
rk.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Exercise:DeployinganAPItotheIncubatorEnvironment-DeployingtoIncub=
ator"><strong>Deploying to Incubator</strong></h2>
<p>Full instructions here:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.c=
om.au/display/MESH/Creating+a+Component+in+the+Incubator+Environment" rel=
=3D"nofollow">Creating a Component in the Incubator Environment</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279632">3=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Developer Responsibilities</=
strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"9e29d552-a56e-4331-b1c4-99c75e54=
37c9-1203279632">
<p><br></p>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"">
<div class=3D"childtabs-macro" data-fixed-position=3D"false">
<div class=3D"aui-tabs horizontal-tabs" data-aui-responsive=3D"true">
<strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data-conte=
nt-id=3D"1203279633">Secure your Component</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"46813f7b-1ba3-46a2-b40f-9f7e663e=
7601-1203279633">
<p>While Westpac Mesh provides support for many network security protocols,=
 it is <strong>your</strong> responsibility as a Developer to ensure that s=
ecure coding practices are followed.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"294" src=3D"8c44a1991c68b3909b796a50d9d1a23ee4399b60186ed796412f7850de=
b5904f" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279633/image2022-9-20_1=
6-39-52.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663655993097&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1202995990" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2022-9-20_16-39-52.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279633" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"3" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"SecureyourComponent-SecureCoding"><strong>Secure Coding</strong><=
/h2>
<p>To deploy code into SVP and Production, your component will need to be d=
igitally signed (this is different to Swagger signing).</p>
<p>When you deploy to SIT, this triggers a Fortify code scan (managed by IS=
G) that checks your code against the latest vulnerabilities. If your code i=
s compliant, your component will be automatically signed.</p>
<p>As a developer, you will need to engage with the ISG representative who =
has been assigned to your team, to register the component in Fortify.</p>
<h2 id=3D"SecureyourComponent-SecretsManagement"><strong>Secrets Management=
</strong></h2>
<p>A key part of secure coding is to manage secrets securely. As a develope=
r, you are responsible for protecting the secrets (such as passwords for fu=
nctional accounts or TLS client certficates) needed by your specific API (s=
ecrets needed for the <em>platform</em> are managed by the platform automat=
ion).</p>
<p>The Westpac Mesh platform provides an end-to-end pattern for management =
of secrets for all environments (with appropriate separation of secrets for=
 each environment).</p>
<p>As a developer you key responsibility is to use the supplied tools to sa=
fely encrypt all secrets in your API configuration.</p>
<p>See&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MESH/How+to+Encrypt+Secrets+Before+Uploadin=
g+Files+to+Bitbucket">How to Encrypt Secrets Before Uploading Files to Bitb=
ucket</a>.&nbsp;<strong>Unencrypted secrets must not be stored in Devops Bi=
tbucket or in Devops Artifactory</strong>.</p>
<h2 id=3D"SecureyourComponent-ThreatModelling"><strong>Threat Modelling</st=
rong></h2>
<p>It is your team's responsibility to identify and document the potential =
security threats against your component, and make efforts to mitigate them.=
</p>
<h2 id=3D"SecureyourComponent-Logging"><strong>Logging</strong></h2>
<p>Any information that your log in your component will appear in Splunk, a=
nd will be visible to anyone that has access.</p>
<p>As standard practice, you should not be logging any usernames and passwo=
rds, and any sensitive personal information such as account numbers, TFNs, =
etc.</p>
<p>Mesh sets the default log level to DEBUG in DEV1 and SIT1, and INFO in U=
AT1, SVP1, and production.</p>
<p>This means that if you log detailed information at DEBUG level in your c=
ode, it will not be logged in production, and logs can be checked in UAT1 b=
efore promoting changes to production.</p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279635">Test your Component</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"46813f7b-1ba3-46a2-b40f-9f7e663e=
7601-1203279635">
<p>Good tests are required to ensure the reliability and stability of your =
API. Westpac Mesh helps automate a lot of the testing for you, but we can o=
nly run the tests which you have actually built.</p>
<p>We maintain an evergreen service, and we recommend regularly rebuilding =
your containers to keep them up to date with the latest patches and platfor=
m features.</p>
<p>In addition to triggering automated tests during CI/CD, we also run them=
 during platform upgrades.</p>
<p>Having good tests helps a lot when investigating and troubleshooting iss=
ues with your component.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"208" src=3D"fce1d0da19890121591dd2a208c4d44588390dca5baebf35e08aeb3166=
07b05e" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279635/image2021-3-31_1=
4-53-34.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571140153&amp;api=3Dv2" =
data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279636" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment"=
 data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-3-31_14-53-34.png" data-ba=
se-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conte=
nt-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279635" data=
-linked-resource-container-version=3D"3" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"TestyourComponent-UnitTests"><strong>Unit Tests</strong></h2>
<p>Junit/Mocha tests are run during Continuous Integration. We also recomme=
nd running these regularly during local development.</p>
<p>Repositories for Java/Nodejs projects will be integrated with Sonarqube.=
 More information can be found here:&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MD/SonarQube+=
Integration">SonarQube Integration</a>.</p>
<p>Currently no quality gates are enforced, it is up to individual project =
teams to decide on their own metrics.</p>
<h2 id=3D"TestyourComponent-APIIntegrationTests"><strong>API Integration Te=
sts</strong></h2>
<p>Postman/Newman tests are run automatically during Continuous Deployment.=
&nbsp;</p>
<p>These tests should be idempotent (should not change the underlying data)=
 as they are run in automated processes.</p>
<p>/healthcheck needs to be implemented correctly and return a HTTP 200 The=
 platform uses this to determine the health of your component.</p>
<p><strong>Guidelines:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MESH/Idempotent+AP=
I+Test+Guidelines">Idempotent API Test Guidelines</a></p>
<h2 id=3D"TestyourComponent-AutomatedFirewallPIVs"><strong>Automated Firewa=
ll PIVs</strong></h2>
<p>These should be setup by project teams to validate backend connectivity =
to any downstream systems your API is dependant on.</p>
<h2 id=3D"TestyourComponent-FunctionalTesting"><strong>Functional Testing</=
strong></h2>
<p>You will likely still require functional testing (UAT) in addition to th=
e automated tests, to cover the full scope of your API.</p>
<p><strong>Guidelines on Full fledge API Testing: <a href=3D"/display/MESH/=
Testing+Microservices">Testing Microservices</a></strong></p>
<h2 id=3D"TestyourComponent-LoadTesting"><strong>Load Testing</strong></h2>
<p>We require SVP load testing to be completed before promotion to Producti=
on.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"236" src=3D"d2288e12e664ab5985a61eda30739095d1a837f6caf14d3c3b5c6f5b4b=
6414f5" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279635/image2021-3-31_1=
4-53-4.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571140220&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279637" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-3-31_14-53-4.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279635" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"3" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279640">Basic Troubleshooting</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"46813f7b-1ba3-46a2-b40f-9f7e663e=
7601-1203279640">
<h2 id=3D"BasicTroubleshooting-InvestigateyourAPIs"><strong>Investigate you=
r APIs</strong></h2>
<p>When the CI/CD pipelines for your APIs fails with an error, be sure to c=
arefully inspect the logging in Bamboo.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The link to the pipelines will be printed on screen by Westpac Mesh Deve=
loper Tools whenever you perform a build or deploy.</p>
<p>You can also find the link in your Bitbucket repository, under the Commi=
ts tab.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"263" src=3D"8f0b4edb5e19d38af4255c51b4dd7832a2fd21f839345eedbb242a794d=
a8fce9" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279640/image2021-5-17_9=
-36-27.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571140917&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279641" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-5-17_9-36-27.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279640" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"3" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Some common errors your could encounter include:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Metadata validation - your component metadata files are scanned and val=
idated to ensure all fields have been entered correctly. You can use Westpa=
c Mesh Developer Tools to perform the same validation before attempting to =
build on the pipeline.</li>
<li>Compile time errors - a Maven build is run on the code in your reposito=
ry, this includes executing any unit tests. Be sure to check that your test=
s have passed.</li>
<li>Deployment errors - your idempotent tests are run each time a deploymen=
t is triggered. Ensure these tests have passed and are correct for the envi=
ronment you are deploying to.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"BasicTroubleshooting-Logging"><strong>Logging</strong></h2>
<p>Mesh includes platform logs to assist troubleshooting, and these help fo=
r generic issues such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>API success / error rates</li>
<li>API performance (average, p50, p90 response times etc)</li>
<li>Correlating requests to identify the root cause for failures</li>
</ul>
<p>Mesh supports flexible component logs for all Mesh components so that de=
velopers can add additional logging to assist in troubleshooting issues.</p=
>
<p>It is important to use appropriate log levels for your logs to ensure th=
at the information you need is logged, error information can be logged, and=
 you can debug issues in development or test.</p>
<p>Mesh assumes that every developer logs as follows:</p>
<ol>
<li>Errors, such as Java Exceptions, are logged at Error level, it is advis=
able to include stack traces for these. Errors are logged in all Mesh envir=
onments.</li>
<li>Summary data for a request is logged at Info level. For example a summa=
ry of the outcome of a request. Info messages are logged in all Mesh enviro=
nments.</li>
<li>Detailed information for debugging is logged at Debug level. For exampl=
e, logs at significant steps in processing, dumps of relevant data etc. Deb=
ug messages are logged in DEV1 and SIT1 (by default).</li>
</ol>
<p>Debug logs can be enabled for a component in UAT1 or SVP1 if needed in (=
rare) cases where issues can't be reproduced in DEV1 or SIT1. This is a dep=
loy-time option.</p>
<p>You&nbsp;<em>don't</em> need to configure logging levels in your Mesh co=
mponent, this actually interferes with the platform levels and can prevent =
us from enabling debug without explicit cofig changes.</p>
<h2 id=3D"BasicTroubleshooting-SampleSplunkqueries"><strong>Sample Splunk q=
ueries</strong></h2>
<p>Splunk collects transaction logs and container logs from all Westpac Mes=
h containers, and allows you to run searches across these logs to identify =
any errors.</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://wbc.splunkcloud.com/en-GB/app/nprd_a008e0/launchpad" =
class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Splunk can be found here.</a>&nbsp=
;You can also find links to a Splunk Dashboard for your particular API from=
 the component details page in Mesh Connect.</p>
<p>The index for Westpac Mesh Production environments is:&nbsp;<span style=
=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>prd_a008e0</strong></span></p>
<p>The index for&nbsp;Westpac Mesh non-Production is:&nbsp;<span style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>nprd_a008e0</strong></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"251" src=3D"62729fab707ee43f9635bd89a30dfd5bbd5b6cf26d154cf5294a3cecab=
db6ea7" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279640/image2021-5-17_9=
-17-44.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571140983&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279642" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2021-5-17_9-17-44.png" data-base=
-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content=
-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279640" data-l=
inked-resource-container-version=3D"3" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p><strong>Return all HTTP 4XX errors</strong></p>
<p>eventtype=3D"gw_internal_transaction_log" OR eventtype=3D"gw_dmz_transac=
tion_log" AND apiName=3Dinf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1 <br>
 | search responseCode!=3DNULL<br>
 | rex field=3DresponseCode "^(?&lt;C4XX&gt;4.*)$"</p>
<p><strong>Return all hits for a particular endpoint</strong></p>
<p>eventtype=3D"gw_internal_transaction_log" OR eventtype=3D"gw_dmz_transac=
tion_log" AND apiName=3Dinf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1 <br>
 | search resourcePath=3D"/componentTypes/{componentType}/components"</p>
<p><strong>All logs for a component</strong></p>
<p>index=3Dnprd_a008e0 environment=3Ddev1 source=3D"/wdp/var/log/containers=
/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1/*"</p>
<p><strong>Component level logs for a component</strong></p>
<p>index=3Dnprd_a008e0 environment=3Ddev1 source=3D"/wdp/var/log/containers=
/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1/*" sourcetype=3D"wdp:component=
"</p>
<p><strong>Container level logs for a component</strong></p>
<p>index=3Dnprd_a008e0 environment=3Ddev1 source=3D"/wdp/var/log/containers=
/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1/*" sourcetype=3D"*:container:w=
dp"</p>
<p><strong>Search by correlation Id</strong></p>
<p>index=3Dnprd_a008e0 environment=3Ddev1 source=3D"/wdp/var/log/containers=
/inf-bnkng-resrcitm-logclitcmpnt-wdpcatlg-v1/*" appCorrelationId=3D"2d4d679=
