</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279645">5=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Other Topics</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"9e29d552-a56e-4331-b1c4-99c75e54=
37c9-1203279645">
<p></p>
<div class=3D"">
<div class=3D"childtabs-macro" data-fixed-position=3D"false">
<div class=3D"aui-tabs horizontal-tabs" data-aui-responsive=3D"true">
<strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data-conte=
nt-id=3D"1203279646">API Communication Patterns</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"6a22a337-d7b0-43d4-b1af-e99d65e7=
7ad4-1203279646">
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" width=
=3D"468" src=3D"a86573aaa6ac0d1e63f139c28b405698e22bf818f29f6c4d52f2b7f2bf9=
a79af" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279646/image2022-9-20_17=
-14-22.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663658062473&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1202996432" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2022-9-20_17-14-22.png" data-bas=
e-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279646" data-=
linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" alt=3D"" height=3D"228"></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"APICommunicationPatterns-InternalGateway"><strong>Internal Gatewa=
y</strong></h2>
<p>This manages all internal traffic between components hosted on Westpac M=
esh. This includes API to API calls, internal consuming applications to an =
API, events from MQ or Kafka to a listener, etc.</p>
<p>Any dependencies and consumptions are defined in dependencies.yaml and c=
onsumption.yaml.</p>
<p>Example:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/w=
dp/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-springapi-v1-api/browse" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/pr=
ojects/wdp/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-springapi-v1-api/browse<=
/a></p>
<p><strong>External Proxy</strong></p>
<p>Components in Westpac Mesh are able to make calls to externally hosted I=
nternet services. This is done via a Proxy API, which contains a swagger, c=
onfiguration for the external service (proxy.yaml), and any secrets, but no=
 code implementation is required.</p>
<p>Example:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/W=
DP/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-apiproxy-v1-api/browse/env/dev1"=
 class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com=
.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-apiproxy-v1-api/br=
owse</a></p>
<p><strong>Internal Proxy</strong></p>
<p>As above, but for a non-Westpac Mesh service hosted in Westpac.</p>
<p><strong>Message Queues</strong></p>
<p>Both Kafka Topics and MQ are supported in Westpac Mesh to help you manag=
e your asynchronous workflows.</p>
<p>Example:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/w=
dp/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-event-v2-topic/browse" class=3D"=
external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projec=
ts/wdp/repos/wdp-cap-technolmgt-pltf-integ-ref-event-v2-topic/browse</a></p=
>
<h2 id=3D"APICommunicationPatterns-ExternalGateway"><strong>External Gatewa=
y</strong></h2>
<p>This gateway sits in the DMZ to handle requests from external consumers.=
 This includes partners and Mesh UIs (hosted on AWS). These requests are mo=
dified with Mesh specific headers and then redirected to the internal gatew=
ay.</p>
<p><strong>Partner Proxy</strong></p>
<p>An API that is called by an external partner in order to reach a service=
 hosted in Westpac Mesh. This API typically has no implementation, and forw=
ards the request to an API on the internal gateway.</p>
<p>Example:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/w=
dp/repos/wdp-ptr-vendor-pltfintegref-apiproxy-v1-api/browse" class=3D"exter=
nal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/wd=
p/repos/wdp-ptr-vendor-pltfintegref-apiproxy-v1-api/browse</a></p>
<p><strong>Consuming Applications</strong></p>
<p>External consumers need to be defined as a Consuming Application compone=
nt in Westpac Mesh. This contain any certificates to authenticate the clien=
t.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Example:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/w=
dp_cons/repos/wdp-ptr-westpac-app-a008e0-referenceapp/browse" class=3D"exte=
rnal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/w=
dp_cons/repos/wdp-ptr-westpac-app-a008e0-referenceapp/browse</a></p>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279648">What are Virtual Swimlanes?</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"6a22a337-d7b0-43d4-b1af-e99d65e7=
7ad4-1203279648">
<h2 id=3D"WhatareVirtualSwimlanes?-VirtualSwimlanes"><strong>Virtual Swimla=
nes</strong></h2>
<p>Swimlanes allows your project team to run parallel streams of developmen=
t, and deploy different builds of the same component to the platform at the=
 same time.</p>
<p>More detailed information about Swimlanes can be found here&nbsp;<a href=
=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Virtual+Swimlanes" r=
el=3D"nofollow">Virtual Swimlanes</a>.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>A step-by-step guide for using Developer Tools to work with Swimlanes ca=
n be found here&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MESH/How+to+Deploy+Your+Components=
+to+Virtual+Swimlanes">How to Deploy Your Components to Virtual Swimlanes</=
a>.</p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"WhatareVirtualSwimlanes?-"><strong><span class=3D"confluence-embe=
dded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence=
-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" height=3D"178" src=3D"e64d3d629b768686=
493029cc9bb276cbf6726d4f76a18207a211edc9e1cad0fd" data-image-src=3D"/downlo=
ad/attachments/1203279648/image2021-5-17_9-9-54.png?version=3D1&amp;modific=
ationDate=3D1663571143797&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0"=
 data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279649" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" =
data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=
=3D"image2021-5-17_9-9-54.png" data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.west=
pac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-res=
ource-container-id=3D"1203279648" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D=
"3" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></strong></h2>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279651">Raising a Service Desk Request</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"6a22a337-d7b0-43d4-b1af-e99d65e7=
7ad4-1203279651">
<h2 id=3D"RaisingaServiceDeskRequest-SelfServices"><strong>Self Services</s=
trong></h2>
<p>The Westpac Mesh platform aims to provide as much self-service as possib=
le. Many common tasks can be managed by developers.</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Build components and deploy to DEV</li>
<li>Deploy components to SIT, UAT</li>
<li>Deploy components to SVP, a ServiceNow change request is required for t=
his</li>
<li>View logs and diagnose component issues</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"RaisingaServiceDeskRequest-ServiceDesk"><strong>Service Desk</str=
ong></h2>
<p>Some activities require privileged access and need to be performed by pl=
atform support staff. These include:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Create a new component repository and link to CI/CD pipelines</li>
<li>Authorising a Consumer Application to access an API</li>
<li>Deploy components to Production, a ServiceNow change request is require=
d for this</li>
</ul>
<p>You can follow the links from <a href=3D"https://mesh.westpac.com.au/" c=
lass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Mesh Connect</a> to raise a service=
 desk request.</p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" width=
=3D"468" src=3D"a40256fff57ac5875ca7b6069342305eb1a8f785892886d2353ed3fdfdc=
10168" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279651/image2022-9-20_17=
-21-25.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663658485890&amp;api=3Dv2" d=
ata-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1202996485" d=
ata-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" =
data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image2022-9-20_17-21-25.png" data-bas=
e-url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279651" data-=
linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" alt=3D"" height=3D"191"></span></p>
<h2 id=3D"RaisingaServiceDeskRequest-InvestigateyourAPIs"><strong>Investiga=
te your APIs</strong></h2>
<p>Always remember to investigate before raising a service desk request! In=
vestigating your API is the Developer's responsibility.</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Check Bamboo logs</li>
<li>Check Splunk logs</li>
<li>Check downstream systems are operational</li>
<li>Do an internet search for your problems (not joking)</li>
</ul>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"1203279653">Westpac Mesh Core Developer Induction Quiz</stro=
ng>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"6a22a337-d7b0-43d4-b1af-e99d65e7=
7ad4-1203279653">
<h2 id=3D"WestpacMeshCoreDeveloperInductionQuiz-Quiz"><strong>Quiz</strong>=
</h2>
<p>What is the file name of your REST API contract?</p>
<ul>
<li>component.yaml</li>
<li>contract.yaml</li>
<li>swagger.yaml</li>
<li>support.yaml</li>
</ul>
<p>What type of tests are run during Continuous Deployment?</p>
<ul>
<li>unit tests</li>
<li>postman tests</li>
<li>load tests</li>
<li>user acceptance testing</li>
</ul>
<p>Which resource must always be implement for your API to work in Westpac =
Mesh?</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>/healthcheck</li>
<li>/heartbeat</li>
<li>/status</li>
<li>/stats</li>
</ul>
<p>Your build has failed during Continuous Integration. What should you do =
first to find the root cause?</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Run 'wdp status' in Developer Tools</li>
<li>Check Splunk dashboards</li>
<li>Check Bamboo logs</li>
<li>Contact service desk</li>
</ul>
<p>What are the two types of digital signatures required before you can per=
form a deployment to SVP? (select all answers that fit)</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Contract signature</li>
<li>Component signature</li>
<li>ISG signature</li>
<li>Mesh signature</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
</div><strong style=3D"text-decoration: underline" class=3D"pageTitle" data=
-content-id=3D"102055681">Proxy use case scenarios</strong>
<div class=3D"tabs-pane active-pane" id=3D"6a22a337-d7b0-43d4-b1af-e99d65e7=
7ad4-102055681">
<p>This page details the different use case scenarios for the proxy depende=
ncies. For architectural overviews please refer to this page: <a href=3D"/d=
isplay/MESH/Supported+Authentication">Supported Authentication</a></p>
<p><style type=3D"text/css">/*<![CDATA[*/
